Freescale's Community Yocto BSP
===============================

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed and use it as:

Install the `repo` utility (only need to do once):
--------------------------------------------------

$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin

Download the BSP Yocto Project Environment into your directory:
-------------------------------------------

$: mkdir fsl-arm-yocto-bsp
$: cd fsl-arm-yocto-bsp
$: repo init -u git://git.freescale.com/imx/fsl-arm-yocto-bsp.git -b imx-4.1.15-1.0.0_genivi-demo
$: repo sync

Setup and Build for Wayland
-------------------------------------------
$: DISTRO=nxp-imx-genivi-wayland MACHINE=imx6qsabreauto source nxp-setup-genivi.sh -b build-genivi

IMAGES
-------------------------------------------
Basic image:
$: bitbake leviathan-image
